    -   Do not interpolate missing data\
    -   Use available data points\
    -   Show real data

-   **Data Filtering**

    1.  **Time**\
        Inequality over time (2000–2023)\
        Differences across countries(2022)\
        Inequality and its associated factors(2021)
    2.  **Country**\

-   **Weighting**
:::

# Terminology {.smaller .with-bottom1}

::: incremental
-   **Gini Coefficient**<sup class="src">1</sup>

    -   Most widely used measure of income inequality\
    -   Range: 0 = perfect equality, 1 = extreme inequality\

-   **Before-tax Income**<sup class="src">1</sup>

    -   Income received before taxes or government transfers\
    -   Reflects market-based income distribution

-   **After-tax Income**<sup class="src">1</sup>

    -   Income after subtracting taxes and adding government transfers\
    -   Indicates resources actually available to households
:::

::: bottom-note1
Source:\[1\] World Bank Poverty and Inequality Platform
:::

